HEADWORD: Succussion
<hw>Suc*cus"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>succussio</ets>, from <ets>succutere</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>succussion</ets>. See <er>Succussation</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
shaking; a shake; esp. <fld>(Med.)</fld>, a shaking of the body to
ascertain if there be a liquid in the thorax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succussive</ent>⟦br⟧
